{[%evp 0,30,18,12,35,6,-7,0,6,-39,-13,-13,-15,-15,-15,-15,-2,-2,-2,-2,-2,-6,-7,-8,8,12,0,-16,-20,-16,-16,-19,-19]} 1. e4 e6 2. c4 (2. f4 $2 {Bad move, a good reaction is} d5 3. e5 d4 $1 {To play for the advantagae.} 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Bb5 Nge7 $15 {Black is just better.}) (2. g3 {Not dangerous.} d5 3. Bg2 dxe4 {The simplest.} 4. Bxe4 Nf6 5. Bg2 e5 $5 {Probably the best, to stop Nf3.} 6. d3 (6. Nf3 $2 e4 $1 $17 {[%csl Rf3]}) 6... Nc6 7. Nf3 e4 $1 {In the endgame, Black is slightly better.} 8. Qe2 Bg4 9. dxe4 Nd4 {The game simplifies.} 10. Qd1 Nxf3+ 11. Bxf3 Qxd1+ 12. Bxd1 Bxd1 13. Kxd1 O-O-O+ $15 {[%cal Gf6e4] If any side can be slightly better, it's Black of course.}) (2. b3 {Jobava spirit move.} d5 3. Bb2 (3. exd5 exd5 $15) 3... Nc6 $1 {[%csl Bc6] Strong move.} (3... dxe4 {If you take, White gets some kind of game.} 4. Nc3 Nf6 5. Qe2 $132 {[%csl Gb2][%cal Ge1c1,Gc3e4] The position becomes playable for White.}) 4. e5 (4. Qe2 $6 dxe4 5. Nc3 Nd4 $1 {reveals the point of the suggested move order, for White is forced to} 6. Qxe4 Nf6 7. Qd3 e5 $1 $36 {[%cal Gc8f5] with fantastic play for Black.}) (4. exd5 exd5 $11 {This is just okay for Black.}) 4... d4 $1 {A good fighting option.} 5. Nf3 (5. Bb5 Nge7 $15 {a6 next.}) 5... a6 {[%cal Rf1b5] To prevent Bb5.} 6. Bd3 g5 $5 $146 {Novelty, and it's slightly better for Black:} (6... f5 $5) 7. Be4 g4 8. Bxc6+ bxc6 9. Nxd4 c5 10. Ne2 Bb7 11. O-O Qd5 12. f3 O-O-O $15 {Nice line, and Black is enjoying life.}) 2... d5 3. exd5 (3. cxd5 exd5 4. Qb3 $6 {This is tried sometimes in blitz/bullet.} dxe4 5. Bc4 Qe7 $1 {A few moves to know and White is just worse.} 6. Nc3 Nf6 7. d3 exd3+ 8. Be3 {Now important move:} d2+ $1 {[%csl Bd2] Nice intermezzo.} 9. Kf1 Nc6 10. Nf3 Bd7 $3 {[%cal Ge8c8] Only move to get an advantage.} 11. Qxb7 (11. Ng5 $2 O-O-O 12. Nxf7 Na5 $19 {Winning position.}) 11... Rb8 12. Qxc7 Rxb2 {Black is better, for example:} 13. Nxd2 (13. Bxd2 Qc5 $19 {[%csl Rc4,Rc7][%cal Gf8d6,Gc5c4]}) 13... Qe5 $17 {The endgame is better for Black, thanks to the active pieces.}) 3... exd5 4. d4 {The best, to transpose to some sort of Exchange French.} (4. cxd5 Nf6 {Precise.} 5. Bb5+ {White at least tries to keep the pawn.} (5. Nc3 Nxd5 6. Nf3 Nc6 {Just very good version of IQP.} 7. d4 Bb4 8. Bd2 O-O 9. Be2 Nf6 $15 {Black is doing great, -0.10 evaluation.}) 5... Nbd7 6. Nc3 a6 7. Be2 {The best.} (7. Ba4 b5 8. Bb3 Bd6 9. Nf3 (9. Qe2+ Qe7 10. Qxe7+ Kxe7 $15 {[%cal Gc8b7,Gd7b6,Gb5b4] The pawn will fall, and Black will be slightly better.}) 9... Qe7+ 10. Qe2 Qxe2+ 11. Kxe2 O-O $15 {[%csl Rd5][%cal Gd7b6,Gc8b7,Gb5b4] Slighlty better endgame.}) 7... Nb6 8. Nf3 Nbxd5 9. O-O Bd6 $11 {Just position, it cannot be problematic for Black.}) 4... Nf6 5. Nc3 Bb4 {The easiest.} 6. Bd3 O-O 7. Nge2 {This is how some GMs play in bullet, I guess to get some premoves in.} (7. Nf3 dxc4 8. Bxc4 Bg4 9. O-O Nc6 10. Be3 Qd6 $11 {Just comfortable for Black.}) 7... dxc4 8. Bxc4 Nbd7 9. O-O Nb6 10. Bb3 c6 11. Bg5 Re8 $1 {[%cal Gc8e6] Good move, with idea of Be6.} 12. Nf4 {To stop the idea.} (12. Qd3 Be6 13. Bxe6 Rxe6 14. Nf4 Re8 15. Nh5 Be7 $11 {Black is completely fine.}) 12... Qd6 13. Nd3 Bg4 14. Qc1 $1 Nfd5 15. Nxb4 Qxb4 $11 {Just equal. On this note, we end our journey in the French Defense for Black, hope it was refreshing for you, and see you soon!} *

